## 4. Feature Flags

Feature flags (also called feature toggles) allow you to **turn features on/off at runtime** without deploying code. They enable trunk‑based development, A/B testing, canary releases, and operational control.

### Types of Feature Flags

| Type | Purpose | Example |
|------|---------|---------|
| **Release Toggles** | Hide unfinished features | `new-checkout-flow` |
| **Experiment Toggles** | A/B test variants | `checkout-button-color` |
| **Ops Toggles** | Disable features during incidents | `disable-recommendations` |
| **Permission Toggles** | Feature access per user/plan | `premium-analytics` |

### LaunchDarkly Integration

```javascript
const LaunchDarkly = require('launchdarkly-node-server-sdk');

const ldClient = await LaunchDarkly.init(process.env.LAUNCHDARKLY_SDK_KEY);

// Middleware to attach LD user
app.use(async (req, res, next) => {
  req.ldUser = {
    key: req.user?.id || req.ip || 'anonymous',
    email: req.user?.email,
    custom: {
      plan: req.user?.plan || 'free',
      region: req.headers['cf-ipcountry'] || 'unknown'
    }
  };
  next();
});

// Feature flag middleware
function featureFlag(flagKey, defaultValue = false) {
  return async (req, res, next) => {
    try {
      req.flags = req.flags || {};
      req.flags[flagKey] = await ldClient.variation(flagKey, req.ldUser, defaultValue);
      next();
    } catch (err) {
      console.error('Feature flag error:', err);
      req.flags[flagKey] = defaultValue;
      next();
    }
  };
}

// Usage in route
app.get('/dashboard', featureFlag('new-dashboard'), (req, res) => {
  if (req.flags['new-dashboard']) {
    return res.render('dashboard-v2');
  }
  res.render('dashboard-v1');
});
```

